            	<h2 class="noTopMargin">Mads Kvalsvik, Founder and CEO</h2>
            	
				<p>Mads has a deep passion for the intersection of business and technology.  He is always looking for better ways to help companies write software.  He started ScandiLabs to help companies put together a well-integrated technology team and build a scalable products.</p>  
				<p>Previously, Mads served as head of new technology ventures for Boathouse Group in Waltham, MA where he led the incubation of several online businesses including the car site SpeedBilly and the social search engine PostPost.</p>
				<p>Earlier he co-founded Savant Technologies, an e-Commerce solutions provider. Savant was later sold to virtual dataroom provider IntraLinks (<a href="http://finance.yahoo.com/q?s=IL">NYSE:IL</a>).  While at IntraLinks Mads led the design and development of the company's flagship SaaS offering and introduced Agile to a 50-person strong team.</p>
				<p>His background also includes work with CNN, Toyota Motors, NPR, BBC Technology, Mohegan Sun, Teradyne, telegea.com, c-tribe.com, and even a one-year stint as an Assistant Professor of object oriented design.  When not helping startups he tries to keep up with his two young boys as a soccer coach.</p> 
				<p>Mads grew up in Norway, and graduated from MIT in 1994.</p>
